# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Repo goes PUBLIC. Anything below is kept on disk for the builder's own
# workflow but is NOT shipped to GitHub — either because it leaks
# hackathon-strategy internals, or because it's AI-agent tooling that
# doesn't belong in the deliverable.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Agent skills & tooling — local dev only, not product artifacts.
.agents/
skills-lock.json

# Milestone entry prompts — these are the recipe the builder used to drive
# successive Claude Code runs. Not a deliverable, and publishing them
# tells the reader "here's how I sequenced Claude to build this."
1st_prompt.md
2nd_prompt.md
3rd_prompt.md
4th_prompt.md
[0-9]*_prompt.md
private_notes/

# Internal hackathon strategy docs. The evaluators reading the repo will
